# Portfolio Project Structure

This Nuxt.js and Directus-based portfolio project has a specific structure and tooling preferences.

## Project Overview

The portfolio consists of two main components:
- `frontend/`: A Nuxt.js application that serves the portfolio website
- `directus/`: A Directus headless CMS for content management

## Development Tools

Always prefer using these tools:

- **doctl**: Digital Ocean CLI for managing deployments
- **Nuxt CLI**: For local development and testing
- **Directus API**: For content management and testing

## Deployment Preferences

- **Build on Deploy**: The application should be built during deployment on Digital Ocean, NOT locally
- **Development Mode**: Enable dev tools when debugging issues with the deployment
- **Error Handling**: Add robust error handling for API calls and data processing

## Documentation References

- @Nuxt Documentation: https://nuxt.com/docs
- @Directus Documentation: https://docs.directus.io/
- @Digital Ocean Docs: https://docs.digitalocean.com/products/app-platform/

## File Structure Conventions

- `frontend/components/`: Vue components organized by feature
- `frontend/composables/`: Shared composition functions
- `frontend/pages/`: Nuxt page components
- `frontend/public/`: Static assets
- `frontend/server/`: Server middleware and API routes
- `directus/`: Directus configuration and extensions 